"title": "5889: ingratitude",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5889",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The absence of due thankfulness. Scripture gives examples of human ingratitude to God for all the blessings and gifts which he provides for them. It is especially important for Christians to give thanks to God.</p>\n<h2>The ingratitude of human beings to one another</h2>\n<h3>Examples of ingratitude</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen40:23\">GEN 40:23</a> <em>the chief butler towards Joseph</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num16:13-Num16:14\">NUM 16:13–16:14</a> <em>Dathan and Abiram to Moses</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg8:35\">JDG 8:35</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg9:18\">JDG 9:18</a>; \n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam25:21\">1SA 25:21</a> <em>Nabal to David</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr24:22\">2CH 24:22</a> <em>King Joash to Jehoiada</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl9:15\">ECC 9:15</a> <em>the citizens to the wise man who delivered a city</em></p>\n<h3>Returning evil for good</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps35:12\">PSA 35:12</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen44:4\">GEN 44:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps109:5\">PSA 109:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov17:13\">PRO 17:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer18:20\">JER 18:20</a></p>\n<h2>Ingratitude to God</h2>\n<h3>It was in evidence at the fall</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen3:2-Gen3:3\">GEN 3:2–3:3</a> <em>Eve showed ingratitude for God's provision by not believing him.</em></p>\n<h3>It is part of fallen human nature</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom1:21\">ROM 1:21</a></strong></p>\n<h3>It is a sign of the last days</h3>\n<p><em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim3:2\">2TI 3:2</a></p>\n<h3>Israel's repeated ingratitude to the LORD</h3>\n<p>For deliverance from Egypt:\n <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod16:3\">EXO 16:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod16:8\">EXO 16:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod17:7\">EXO 17:7</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb3:7-Heb3:9\">HEB 3:7–3:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb3:15\">HEB 3:15</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps95:7-Ps95:9\">PSA 95:7–95:9</a>; \n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut32:6\">DEU 32:6</a> <em>They were rebuked by Moses for the way they repaid God</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam8:7-1Sam8:8\">1SA 8:7–8:8</a> <em>They rejected the LORD when they rejected Samuel</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh9:26\">NEH 9:26</a> <em>They rejected God's law and killed his prophets.</em></p>\n<h2>Ingratitude compared with other sins</h2>\n<h3>Becoming like animals</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa1:3\">ISA 1:3</a></p>\n<h3>Becoming like prostitutes</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek16:17-Ezek16:19\">EZK 16:17–16:19</a></p>\n<h3>Becoming like an adulterous wife</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos2:8\">HOS 2:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos4:12\">HOS 4:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos5:4\">HOS 5:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos9:1\">HOS 9:1</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ exposed ingratitude</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke17:15-Luke17:18\">LUK 17:15–17:18</a></p>\n<h2>God is kind even to the ungrateful</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke6:35\">LUK 6:35</a></p>\n<h2>It is important for believers to show gratitude to God</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps100:4\">PSA 100:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps107:22\">PSA 107:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col1:12\">COL 1:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col3:15\">COL 3:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess5:18\">1TH 5:18</a></p>",
